							<h1><a href="#overview" class="active">Overview</a><a href="#submit">Submission</a><a href="#result">Result</a></h1>
							<div id="overview" class="active content clearfix">
								<p>
									Thanks to the extraordinary development over the past 30 years, today's China has arrived at a key turning point of its growth, with tremendous opportunities for entrepreneurs. At the same time, this rapid growth has also revealed a number of issues in modern China's development. Budding entrepreneurs around the world seek to seize this opportunity to utilize innovation with a global vision and solid technology to address many of these issues. Being at these historical crossroads, MIT-CHIEF (MIT-China Innovation and Entrepreneurship Forum) presents to you the MIT-CHIEF "Pitch to China" Business Plan Contest, striving to foster connections of new technologies and business models with investment funding and execution experience from China and outside. We are dedicated to facilitating overseas entrepreneurs with resources within China and helping them both enter the Chinese market as well as bring about positive change for both China and the world as a whole.
								</p>
								<p>
									6 teams will enter the final competition for a total of $18,000 in cash prizes, no strings attached!
								</p>
								<ul>
									<li>
										First prize (1 team): $10,000
									</li>
									<li>
										Second prize (2 teams): $2,500 each
									</li>
									<li>
										Third prize (3 teams): $1,000 each
									</li>
								</ul>
								<p>
									Contestants will also be able to:
								</p>
								<ul>
									<li>
										Have an opportunity to present business ideas, and receive feedback from experienced entrepreneurs and investors from both China and abroad
									</li>
									<li>
										Exchange ideas with invited guests of MIT-CHIEF, including researchers, well-known entrepreneurs, and policy-makers.
									</li>
									<li>
										Have an opportunity to receive critiques and advice from investors, successful entrepreneurs, professors, and lawyers.
									</li>
									<li>
										Promote business plans to the mass media and potential customers.
									</li>
									<li>
										Attend lectures at MIT-CHIEF given by well-known MIT scholars, seasoned entrepreneurs, and lawyers.
									</li>
									<li>
										Present their business ideas at a poster exhibition at the MIT-CHIEF conference.
									</li>
									<li>
										Gain access to entrepreneurial resources from our partners to accelerate their businesses.
									</li>
									<li>
										Meet face to face with representatives from industrial parks and high-tech zones in China.
									</li>
								</ul>
								<p>
									Let's pitch to China and bridge innovative ideas and talents between China and US!
								</p>
								<p>
									Please contact contest at mitchief.org for more information.
								</p>
								<h2>Eligibility</h2>
								<p>
									Any individual or team aiming to develop the China market by using innovative technologies and business models and seeking funding from Chinese investors.
								</p>
								<h2>How to Enroll</h2>
								<ol>
									<li>
										Register yourself or your team <a href="contest-submit">here</a>.
									</li>
									<li>
										Before Sept. 12th 23:00 EST, fill out required information on the submission page and upload your executive summary (either less than 2 pages word document or less than 12 pages deck) in PDF format, which includes but not limited to the answers of the following questions:
										<ul>
											<li>What is the problem you try to solve?</li>
											<li>What is your solution?</li>
											<li>who is the customer?</li>
											<li>what is the market opportunity?</li>
											<li>Who is your potential competitor?</li>
											<li>what is your competitive advantage?</li>
											<li>how to generate revenue?</li>
											<li>who is your team members?</li>
										</ul>
										You can find a template at our Resource page.
									</li>
									<li>
										Upon semi-finalist announcement, the contest committee will contact you through mail or phone for further instructions.
									</li>
								</ol>
								<p>
									On stage presentation is required for the finale . In case finalist cannot attend the finale, please contact the contest committee immediately.
								</p>
