								<h2>FAQ</h2>
								<dl>
									<dt>
										What is MIT-CHIEF Business Plan Contest?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										The MIT-CHIEF Business Plan Contest is a major component of MIT-CHIEF. It serves as platforms to connect young entrepreneurs in the US and potential investors from China. The Business Plan Contest aims at helping participants to develop and sharpen their business ideas by meeting with our China market experts and getting in touch with potential investors from China.
									</dd>
									<dt>
										What are we looking for?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										We are looking for new business models and technologies which have potential to be applied to China’s market. Technology holders are encouraged to apply for the Business Plan Contest.
									</dd>
									<dt>
										Who are eligible?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										MIT-CHIEF Business Plan Contest is open to all part-time and full-time students and young startups. If you have brilliant ideas, whether you have ongoing project or already launched company, whether your industry is Information Technology, Clean Energy, Medical, Biology, new business model, social entrepreneurship, or others, you are more than welcome to join us!
									</dd>
									<dt>
										What are the benefits of joining the contest?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										Besides cash rewards, winners of the contest will have good chances to receive angel funding after discussing their business plans with China Venture Capitalists and Angel Investors. Although we cannot foresee how many successful investments will be made through this contest, we will ensure it to be a fulfilling and instructive process for the participants. Finalists of the Entrepreneurship Contests will receive mentors from experienced business practitioners and MIT faculties. Finalists will be invited to a network session with our guest speakers and judges.
									</dd>
									<dt>
										Is it required to submit the executive summary in both Chinese and English?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										Contestants should use the language that they are most comfortable with, which explains their ideas clearly and accurately. It’s not necessary to submit the executive summary in both languages.
									</dd>
									<dt>
										What are the judging criteria?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										Judges will evaluate projects upon a number of criteria, including but not limited to feasibility, innovativeness, technology, China market focus and the teamwork.
									</dd>
									<dt>
										Are there any training opportunities?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										We provide some resources that may be useful for all contestants. For semi-finalists onwards, we will provide a course of entrepreneurship fundamentals, and a lecture of Entrepreneurship in the Technology Sector and Law.
									</dd>
									<dt>
										If I have different projects, how can I register?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										In principle we recommend you submit one project under one registered account. If you do need to submit multiple projects, please contact the Contest Organizing Committee.
									</dd>
									<dt>
										Is it possible to upload a new executive summary and business plan after the first submission?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										You can re-submit the updated version after login.
									</dd>
									<dt>
										Can I register for the contest if I am international?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										The first and second round of judging occurs online and can be completed remotely from anywhere in the world. The finale will require the contestants to be physically present on stage.
									</dd>
									<dt>
										What I should do if I could not attend contest onsite?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										Please contact the Contest Organizing Committee as your earliest convenience.
									</dd>
									<dt>
										How do I get more information on MIT-CHIEF Business Plan Contest?
									</dt>
									<dd>
										Follow us on Facebook, LinkedIn, Twitter, and Weibo. If you have a specific request and/or question that isn’t addressed on our website or social networking sites, please send an email inquiry to: contest [at] mitchief.org.
									</dd>
